{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969292,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uqgcHE2Ah5G54FG1CWrJZ0hl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\n5: argument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\n6: version: 1.11.0.0\n7: ---\n8: <!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n9: \n10: <!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n11: \n12: # Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n13: \n14: Iterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n15: \n16: Runtime path resolution:\n17: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n18: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n19: - OpenCode runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.toml` when running directly in OpenCode; external OpenCode dispatch uses `cli-opencode`.\n20: \n21: Convergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n22: \n23: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n24: \n25: ### When to Use This Skill\n26: \n27: Use this skill when:\n28: - Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n29: - Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n30: - Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n31: - Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n32: - Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n33: - Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n34: - Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n35: \n36: ### When NOT to Use\n37: \n38: - Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n39: - Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n40: - Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n41: - Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n42: - Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n43: \n44: ### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n45: \n46: This skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n47: \n48: **NEVER:**\n49: - Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n50: - Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n51: - Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n52: - Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n53: - Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n54: - Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n55: \n56: **COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n57: \n58: **ALWAYS:**\n59: - Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n60: - Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n61: - Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n62: - Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n63: - Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n64: \n65: ### Trigger Phrases\n66: \n67: - \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n68: - \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n69: - \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n70: - \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n71: - \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n72: - \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n73: - \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n74: \n75: ### Keyword Triggers\n76: \n77: `deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n82: \n83: \n84: ### Resource Loading Levels\n85: \n86: | Level | When to Load | Resources |\n87: |-------|-------------|-----------|\n88: | ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n89: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n90: | ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n91: \n92: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n93: \n94: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n95: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n96: - Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n97: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: from pathlib import Path\n101: \n102: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n103: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n104: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n105: \n106: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n107:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n108:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n109:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n110:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n111: }\n112: \n113: NOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n114:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n115:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n116:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n117:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n118: }\n119: \n120: # RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\n121: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n122:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n123:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n124:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n125:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n126:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n127:         \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n128:     ],\n129:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n130:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n131:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n132:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n133:     ],\n134:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n135:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n136:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n137:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n138:     ],\n139:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n140:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n141:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n142:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n143:         \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n144:     ],\n145: }\n146: \n147: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n148:     \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n149:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n150:     \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n151:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n152:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n153:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n154:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n155:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n156:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n157:     ],\n158: }\n159: \n160: PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n161:     \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n162:     \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n163:     \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n164:     \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n165: }\n166: \n167: NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n168:     \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n169: }\n170: \n171: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n172:     \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n173:     \"Confirm the review phase\",\n174:     \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n175:     \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n176: ]\n177: \n178: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n179:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n180:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n181:     if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n182:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n183:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n184: \n185: def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n186:     docs = []\n187:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n188:         if base.exists():\n189:             docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n190:     return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n191: \n192: def get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n193:     phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n194:     if phase:\n195:         return phase\n196:     text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n197:     if \"recovery\" in text:\n198:         return \"stuck\"\n199:     if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n200:         return \"synthesis\"\n201:     if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n202:         return \"iteration\"\n203:     return \"init\"\n204: \n205: def route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n206:     inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n207:     routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n208:     scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n209:     intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n210: \n211:     loaded = []\n212:     seen = set()\n213: \n214:     def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n215:         guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n216:         if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n217:             load(guarded)\n218:             loaded.append(guarded)\n219:             seen.add(guarded)\n220: \n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 501. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- OpenCode runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.toml` when running directly in OpenCode; external OpenCode dispatch uses `cli-opencode`.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- OpenCode runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.toml` when running directly in OpenCode; external OpenCode dispatch uses `cli-opencode`.\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n- Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n\n### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n\nThis skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n- Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n- Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n- Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n- Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n- Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n\n**COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n- Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n- Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n- Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n- Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n\n### Trigger Phrases\n\n- \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n- \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n- \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n- \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n- \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n- \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n- \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n`deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n}\n\n# RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nPHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n}\n\nNON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n    \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n    \"Confirm the review phase\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n    phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n    if phase:\n        return phase\n    text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if \"recovery\" in text:\n        return \"stuck\"\n    if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n        return \"synthesis\"\n    if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n        return \"iteration\"\n    return \"init\"\n\ndef route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n    scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":501,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782918969274,"end":1782918969289}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f3927488191bc52c27bb06cba25"}},"id":"prt_f1e407785001jr17WS71nidxzW","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969331,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lxJM9RkrcSoFYQd85WGhHGQu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review quick reference\"\n6:   - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n8:   - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n9:   - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: version: 1.11.0.16\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Quick Reference\n16: \n17: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n30: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n31: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n32: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n33: \n34: ### Commands\n35: \n36: | Command | Description |\n37: |---------|-------------|\n38: | `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n39: | `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n40: | `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n41: \n42: ### Parameters\n43: \n44: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n45: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n46: | `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n47: | `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n48: | `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n49: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n50: | `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n51: | `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 2. WHEN TO USE\n56: \n57: | Scenario | Use |\n58: |----------|-----|\n59: | Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n60: | Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n61: | Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n62: | Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n63: | Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n68: \n69: ```\n70: /deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n71:     |                    |                      |\n72:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n73:     |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n74:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n75:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n76:     |                    |\n77:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n78:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n79:     |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n80:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 4. STATE FILES\n86: \n87: Review mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n88: \n89: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n90: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n91: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n92: | State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n93: | Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n94: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n95: | Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n96: | Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n97: | Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n98: | Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n99: \n100: ### Lifecycle Modes\n101: \n102: | Mode | Effect |\n103: |------|--------|\n104: | `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n105: | `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n106: | `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n107: | `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n112: \n113: | ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n114: |----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n115: | D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n116: | D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n117: | D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n118: | D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n123: \n124: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n125: |---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n126: | FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n127: | CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n128: | PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n129: \n130: ### Release Readiness\n131: \n132: `releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n133: \n134: | State | Meaning |\n135: |-------|---------|\n136: | `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n137: | `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n138: | `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n143: \n144: | Gate | Rule |\n145: |------|------|\n146: | Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n147: | Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n148: | Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n153: \n154: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n155: |--------|--------|-------------|\n156: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n157: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n158: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n159: \n160: **Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n161: \n162: **P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n167: \n168: Each @deep-review iteration:\n169: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n170: 2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n171: 3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n172: 4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n173: 5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n174: 6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n175: 7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n180: \n181: | # | Section | Purpose |\n182: |---|---------|---------|\n183: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n184: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n185: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n186: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n187: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n188: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n189: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n190: | 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n191: | 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n196: \n197: | Goal | Adjustment |\n198: |------|------------|\n199: | Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n200: | Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n201: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n202: | Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n203: | Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n208: \n209: | Problem | Fix |\n210: |---------|-----|\n211: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n212: | Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n213: | P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n214: | Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n215: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## 13. RELATED\n220: \n221: | Resource | Purpose |\n222: |----------|---------|\n223: | `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n224: | `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n225: | `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n226: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n227: | `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n228: \n229: For review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n230: - `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n231: - `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n232: - `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms\n\n(End of file - total 232 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n- Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n- Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n- Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n\n### Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n| `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n| `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n\n---\n\n## 2. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n| Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n| Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n| Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n| Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```\n/deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE FILES\n\nReview mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n| State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n| Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n| Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n| Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n| Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n\n### Lifecycle Modes\n\n| Mode | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n| `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n| `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n| `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\n| ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n|----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n| D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n| D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n| D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n\n---\n\n## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Release Readiness\n\n`releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n| `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n| `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n| Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n| Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n\n**Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n\n**P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n\n---\n\n## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-review iteration:\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n\n---\n\n## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n| Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n| Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n\n---\n\n## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n| Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n| P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n| Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n\n---\n\n## 13. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n| `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n| `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n| `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n\nFor review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n- `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n- `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n- `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":232,"totalLines":232,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1782918969314,"end":1782918969330}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f39276c81918790441da4ba0ab1"}},"id":"prt_f1e4077bc001gngpbEn6CGeflG","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969334,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FhlX7Ve8Z9N7vrpn4VSvXISF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"review loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"review auto resume\"\n9:   - \"review synthesis phase\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\n16: \n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n36: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n37: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n38: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n39: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n40: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n41: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n42: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n43: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n44: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n45: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n46: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n47: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n48: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n50: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n51: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Core Innovation\n55: \n56: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n57: \n58: ### Key References\n59: \n60: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n61: |----------|------|---------|\n62: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n63: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n64: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n65: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n66: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n71: \n72: ### Purpose\n73: \n74: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n75: \n76: ### Steps\n77: \n78: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n79:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n80:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n81:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n82:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n83: \n84: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n85: \n86: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n87: \n88:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n89:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n90:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n91:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n92:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n93:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n94:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n95: \n96:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n97: \n98: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n99: \n100:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n101:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\n102:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n103:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n104:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n105:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n106: \n107:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n108: \n109: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n110: \n111:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n112:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n113:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n114:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n115:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n116:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n117:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n118:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n119: \n120:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n121: \n122: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n123: \n124: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n125: \n126: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n127: \n128: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n129:    - Topic (review target description)\n130:    - Review Dimensions checklist\n131:    - Files Under Review table\n132:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n133:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n134:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n135:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n136:    - Review Boundaries from config\n137: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n138:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n139:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n140: \n141: 10. **Validate review charter**:\n142:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n143:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n144:    - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n145: \n146: 11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n147: \n148: ### Outputs\n149: \n150: | File | Location | Purpose |\n151: |------|----------|---------|\n152: | Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n153: | State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n154: | Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n155: | Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n160: \n161: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n162: \n163: #### Step 1: Read State\n164: \n165: - Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n166: - Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n167: - Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n168: \n169: Reducer contract for every loop refresh:\n170: \n171: | Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n172: |--------------|-----------------|-------|\n173: | Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n174: | Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n175: | Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n176: \n177: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n178: \n179: Run `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n180: \n181: - Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n182: - Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n183: - Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n184:   - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n185:   - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n186:   - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n187:   - Required traceability protocols are covered\n188:   - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n189: - Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n190: \n191: If convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n192: \n193: - `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n194: - `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n195: - `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n196: \n197: The blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n198: \n199: Convergence signals and weights:\n200: \n201: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n202: |--------|--------|-------------|\n203: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n204: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n205: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n206: \n207: **P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n208: \n209: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n210: \n211: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n212: \n213: 1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n214: 2. If present:\n215:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n216:    - Halt the loop with message:\n217:      ```\n218:      Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n219:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n220:      ```\n221:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n222: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n223:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n224:    - Continue from step_read_state\n225: \n226: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n227: \n228: Normalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n229: \n230: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n231: \n232: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n233: \n234: ```\n235: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\n236: Iteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\n237: Target: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\n238: Dimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\n239: Findings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\n240: Traceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\n241: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n242: Provisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\n243: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n244: ```\n245: \n246: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n247: \n248: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n249: \n250: Dispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n251: \n252: ```\n253: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n254: \n255: Review Target: {config.reviewTarget}\n256: Review Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\n259: Focus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\n260: Remaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 766. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n- Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n- Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n- Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n│              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n│ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n│ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n│ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n│ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n│ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n│              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n└──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Innovation\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Key References\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n| Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n| Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\n\nSet up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n\n2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n\n3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n\n   | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n   |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n   | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n   | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n   | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n   | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n   | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n\n   Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n\n4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n\n   | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n   |----------|-----------|-----------|\n   | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n   | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n   | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n   | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n\n   Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n\n5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n\n   | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n   |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n   | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n   | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n   | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n   | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n   | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n   | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n\n   Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n\n6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n\n7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n\n8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n\n9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n   - Topic (review target description)\n   - Review Dimensions checklist\n   - Files Under Review table\n   - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n   - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n   - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n   - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n   - Review Boundaries from config\n9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n   - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n\n10. **Validate review charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n\n11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n\n### Outputs\n\n| File | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n| State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n| Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n| Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n\n- Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n- Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n- Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n\nReducer contract for every loop refresh:\n\n| Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n|--------------|-----------------|-------|\n| Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n| Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n| Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\n\nRun `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n\n- Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n- Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n- Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n  - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n  - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n  - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n  - Required traceability protocols are covered\n  - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n- Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n\nIf convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n- `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n- `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n\nThe blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n\nConvergence signals and weights:\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n\n**P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```\n     Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n\nNormalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\nIteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\nTarget: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\nDimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\nFindings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\nTraceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nProvisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n\nDispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n\n```\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nReview Target: {config.reviewTarget}\nReview Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\nFocus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\nRemaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":766,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1782918969322,"end":1782918969332}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f39277c81918567a4a2115048dd"}},"id":"prt_f1e4077e3001UiVbONeYPwMpJg","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969348,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6thnba9mDcvEjGDyFjiU8woI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state format\"\n6:   - \"deep review config schema\"\n7:   - \"review severity weights\"\n8:   - \"file protection levels\"\n9:   - \"review iteration file structure\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.28\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review State Format\n16: \n17: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n24: \n25: | File | Format | Mutability |\n26: |------|--------|------------|\n27: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n28: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n29: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n30: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n31: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n32: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n33: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n35: \n36: ```text\n37: {artifact_dir}/\n38:   deep-review-config.json\n39:   deep-review-state.jsonl\n40:   deep-review-findings-registry.json\n41:   deep-review-strategy.md\n42:   deep-review-dashboard.md\n43:   .deep-review-pause\n44:   review-report.md\n45:   iterations/\n46:     iteration-001.md\n47:     iteration-002.md\n48:     ...\n49: ```\n50: \n51: `{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n52: \n53: ### When to Use\n54: \n55: - Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n56: - Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n57: - Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n58: - Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n63: \n64: Created during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n65: \n66: ```json\n67: {\n68:   \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n69:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n70:   \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n71:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n72:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n73:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n74:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n75:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n76:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n77:   \"generation\": 1,\n78:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n79:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n80:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n81:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n82:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n83:   \"crossReference\": {\n84:     \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n85:     \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n86:   },\n87:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n88:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n89:   \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n90:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n91:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n92:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n93:   \"fileProtection\": {\n94:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n95:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n96:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n97:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n98:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n99:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n100:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n101:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n102:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n103:   },\n104:   \"reducer\": {\n105:     \"enabled\": true,\n106:     \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n107:     \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n108:     \"metrics\": [\n109:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n110:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n111:       \"openFindings\",\n112:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n113:       \"convergenceScore\"\n114:     ]\n115:   }\n116: }\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Field Reference\n120: \n121: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n122: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n123: | mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n124: | reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n125: | reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n126: | reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n127: | resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n128: | sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n129: | parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n130: | lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n131: | generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n132: | continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n133: | maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n134: | convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n135: | stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n136: | severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n137: | crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n138: | qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n139: | specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n140: | status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n141: | releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n142: | fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n143: | reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n144: \n145: ### File Protection Levels\n146: \n147: | Level | Meaning |\n148: |-------|---------|\n149: | immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n150: | append-only | New content added at end only |\n151: | mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n152: | write-once | Created once, never modified |\n153: | auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n154: | operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n155: \n156: ### Review Dimensions\n157: \n158: | Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n159: |-----------|----------|---------------------|\n160: | correctness | 1 | Yes |\n161: | security | 2 | Yes |\n162: | traceability | 3 | Yes |\n163: | maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n164: \n165: ### Severity Weights\n166: \n167: | Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n168: |----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n169: | P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n170: | P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n171: | P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## 3. STATE LOG\n176: \n177: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n182: \n183: Updated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n184: \n185: ### Required Sections\n186: \n187: | Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n188: |---------|-----------|---------|\n189: | topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n190: | review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n191: | completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n192: | running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n193: | what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n194: | what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n195: | exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n196: | ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n197: | next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n198: | known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n199: | cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n200: | files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n201: | review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n202: \n203: ### Mapping from Research Mode\n204: \n205: | Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n206: |---------------|-------------------|\n207: | review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n208: | completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n209: | running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n210: | cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n211: | files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n212: | review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n213: \n214: Sections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n215: \n216: ### Update Protocol\n217: \n218: 1. Read current strategy file\n219: 2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n220: 3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n221: 4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n222: 5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n223: 6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n228: \n229: Reducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n230: \n231: ```json\n232: {\n233:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n234:   \"generation\": 1,\n235:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n236:   \"openFindings\": [],\n237:   \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n238:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n239:   \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n240:   \"severityChanged\": [],\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 544. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n| `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n| `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n\n```text\n{artifact_dir}/\n  deep-review-config.json\n  deep-review-state.jsonl\n  deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  deep-review-strategy.md\n  deep-review-dashboard.md\n  .deep-review-pause\n  review-report.md\n  iterations/\n    iteration-001.md\n    iteration-002.md\n    ...\n```\n\n`{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n- Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n- Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n- Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n\nCreated during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n    \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n    \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Field Reference\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n| reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n| reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n| reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n| resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n| sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n| parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n| lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n| generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n| continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n| maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n| convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n| stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n| qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n| specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n| status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n| releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n| fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n| reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n\n### File Protection Levels\n\n| Level | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n| append-only | New content added at end only |\n| mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n| write-once | Created once, never modified |\n| auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n| operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|---------------------|\n| correctness | 1 | Yes |\n| security | 2 | Yes |\n| traceability | 3 | Yes |\n| maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n| P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n| P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n| P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## 3. STATE LOG\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n\nUpdated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n\n### Required Sections\n\n| Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n| review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n| completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n| running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n| what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n| what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n| exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n| ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n| next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n| known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n| cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n| files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n| review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n\n### Mapping from Research Mode\n\n| Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n| completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n| running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n\nSections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n\n### Update Protocol\n\n1. Read current strategy file\n2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n\nReducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"openFindings\": [],\n  \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n  \"severityChanged\": [],","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":544,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1782918969344,"end":1782918969347}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f3927b88191bf6582134618371c"}},"id":"prt_f1e4077f700128MbxdBLAORmu2","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969371,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a0wHLfCpsPRMviylHtPAjPpu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\nplan.md\nresearch/\nreview/\nspec.md\n\n(4 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"plan.md\nresearch/\nreview/\nspec.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit","entries":["plan.md","research/","review/","spec.md"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":4,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit","time":{"start":1782918969368,"end":1782918969370}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f3928288191a35654ec6fa8770d"}},"id":"prt_f1e407817001gxn95SAZ7k11DS","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969382,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gjdmwomuw714rx8SeqQ3iXGd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.3\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Outputs\n15: \n16: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n27: \n28: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n29: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n30: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n31: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n32: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n33: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n34: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n35: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n36: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n37: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n42: \n43: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n44: \n45: ```text\n46: Review verdict: PASS\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ```text\n50: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ```text\n54: Review verdict: FAIL\n55: ```\n56: \n57: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n62: \n63: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n64: \n65: - Current iteration and next focus.\n66: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n67: - Dimension coverage.\n68: - Convergence trend.\n69: - Gate blockers.\n70: - Provisional verdict.\n71: \n72: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n77: \n78: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n79: \n80: - Executive summary.\n81: - Planning trigger.\n82: - Active finding registry.\n83: - Remediation workstreams.\n84: - Spec seed.\n85: - Plan seed.\n86: - Traceability status.\n87: - Deferred items.\n88: - Audit appendix.\n89: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n94: \n95: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n96: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n97: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1782918969356,"end":1782918969378}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f3927e081919a4226490cd27567"}},"id":"prt_f1e407806001ji7Q8ECzjlEYc7","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969382,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mt8H38qq2qsAdDyMBISb41Kp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n2: # This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n3: # convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n4: # and validation expectations.\n5: \n6: meta:\n7:   ownerSkill: deep-review\n8:   reviewModeVersion: 2\n9:   generatedNotice:\n10:     warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n11:     beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n12:     endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n13:   sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n14: \n15: # Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\n16: contract:\n17:   defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n18: \n19:   # Review target taxonomy.\n20:   targetTypes:\n21:     - id: spec-folder\n22:       cliValue: spec-folder\n23:       label: Spec Folder\n24:       description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n25:     - id: skill\n26:       cliValue: skill\n27:       label: Skill\n28:       description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n29:     - id: agent\n30:       cliValue: agent\n31:       label: Agent\n32:       description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n33:     - id: track\n34:       cliValue: track\n35:       label: Track\n36:       description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n37:     - id: files\n38:       cliValue: files\n39:       label: Files\n40:       description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n41: \n42:   # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n43:   # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n44:   dimensions:\n45:     - id: correctness\n46:       priority: 1\n47:       label: Correctness\n48:       checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n49:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n50:     - id: security\n51:       priority: 2\n52:       label: Security\n53:       checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n54:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n55:     - id: traceability\n56:       priority: 3\n57:       label: Traceability\n58:       checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n59:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n60:     - id: maintainability\n61:       priority: 4\n62:       label: Maintainability\n63:       checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n64:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n65: \n66:   # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n67:   severities:\n68:     - id: P0\n69:       weight: 10.0\n70:       label: Blocker\n71:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n72:     - id: P1\n73:       weight: 5.0\n74:       label: Required\n75:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n76:     - id: P2\n77:       weight: 1.0\n78:       label: Suggestion\n79:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n80: \n81:   # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n82:   verdicts:\n83:     - id: FAIL\n84:       label: Fail\n85:       condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n86:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n87:     - id: CONDITIONAL\n88:       label: Conditional\n89:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n90:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n91:     - id: PASS\n92:       label: Pass\n93:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n94:       hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n95:       nextCommand: /create:changelog\n96: \n97:   # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n98:   qualityGates:\n99:     - id: evidence\n100:       label: Evidence\n101:       binary: true\n102:       combines:\n103:         - evidence-completeness\n104:         - no-inference-only\n105:       rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n106:     - id: scope\n107:       label: Scope\n108:       binary: true\n109:       combines:\n110:         - scope-alignment\n111:       rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n112:     - id: coverage\n113:       label: Coverage\n114:       binary: true\n115:       combines:\n116:         - severity-coverage\n117:         - cross-reference\n118:       rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n119: \n120:   # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n121:   convergence:\n122:     defaults:\n123:       maxIterations: 7\n124:       convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n125:       stuckThreshold: 2\n126:     signals:\n127:       - id: rolling-average\n128:         weight: 0.30\n129:         description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n130:       - id: mad-noise-floor\n131:         weight: 0.25\n132:         description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n133:       - id: dimension-coverage\n134:         weight: 0.45\n135:         description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n136:     severityMath:\n137:       refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n138:       p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n139:       noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n140:     coverageAge:\n141:       minStabilizationPasses: 1\n142:     thresholds:\n143:       rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n144:       noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n145:       compositeStopScore: 0.60\n146: \n147:   lifecycleModes:\n148:     - id: new\n149:       description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n150:     - id: resume\n151:       description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n152:     - id: restart\n153:       description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n154:     - id: fork\n155:       status: deferred\n156:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n157:     - id: completed-continue\n158:       status: deferred\n159:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n160: \n161:   lineageFields:\n162:     - sessionId\n163:     - parentSessionId\n164:     - lineageMode\n165:     - generation\n166:     - continuedFromRun\n167: \n168:   reducer:\n169:     enabled: true\n170:     inputs:\n171:       - latestJSONLDelta\n172:       - newIterationFile\n173:       - priorReducedState\n174:     outputs:\n175:       - findingsRegistry\n176:       - dashboardMetrics\n177:       - strategyUpdates\n178:     failureModes:\n179:       malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n180:       missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n181:       schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n182:     idempotent: true\n183: \n184:   releaseReadinessStates:\n185:     - id: in-progress\n186:       description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n187:     - id: converged\n188:       description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n189:     - id: release-blocking\n190:       description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n191: \n192:   # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n193:   # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n194:   crossReferenceProtocols:\n195:     - id: spec_code\n196:       dimension: traceability\n197:       level: core\n198:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n199:       gateClass: hard\n200:       passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n201:       partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n202:       failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n203:     - id: checklist_evidence\n204:       dimension: traceability\n205:       level: core\n206:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n207:       gateClass: hard\n208:       passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n209:       partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n210:       failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n211:     - id: skill_agent\n212:       dimension: traceability\n213:       level: overlay\n214:       appliesTo: [skill]\n215:       gateClass: advisory\n216:       passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n217:       partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n218:       failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n219:     - id: agent_cross_runtime\n220:       dimension: traceability\n221:       level: overlay\n222:       appliesTo: [agent]\n223:       gateClass: advisory\n224:       passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n225:       partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n226:       failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n227:     - id: feature_catalog_code\n228:       dimension: traceability\n229:       level: overlay\n230:       appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n231:       gateClass: advisory\n232:       passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n233:       partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n234:       failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n235:     - id: playbook_capability\n236:       dimension: traceability\n237:       level: overlay\n238:       appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n239:       gateClass: advisory\n240:       passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n241:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n242:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n243: \n244:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n245:   outputs:\n246:     config:\n247:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n248:       machineOwned: false\n249:       fields:\n250:         - sessionId\n251:         - parentSessionId\n252:         - lineageMode\n253:         - generation\n254:         - continuedFromRun\n255:         - releaseReadinessState\n256:     findingsRegistry:\n257:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n258:       machineOwned: true\n259:       sections:\n260:         - openFindings\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 481. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n    beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n    endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","text":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n    beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n    endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:\n    - id: spec-folder\n      cliValue: spec-folder\n      label: Spec Folder\n      description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n    - id: skill\n      cliValue: skill\n      label: Skill\n      description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n    - id: agent\n      cliValue: agent\n      label: Agent\n      description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n    - id: track\n      cliValue: track\n      label: Track\n      description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n    - id: files\n      cliValue: files\n      label: Files\n      description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n\n  # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n  # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n  dimensions:\n    - id: correctness\n      priority: 1\n      label: Correctness\n      checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: security\n      priority: 2\n      label: Security\n      checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: traceability\n      priority: 3\n      label: Traceability\n      checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n    - id: maintainability\n      priority: 4\n      label: Maintainability\n      checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n\n  # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n  severities:\n    - id: P0\n      weight: 10.0\n      label: Blocker\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P1\n      weight: 5.0\n      label: Required\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P2\n      weight: 1.0\n      label: Suggestion\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n\n  # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n  verdicts:\n    - id: FAIL\n      label: Fail\n      condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: CONDITIONAL\n      label: Conditional\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: PASS\n      label: Pass\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n      hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n      nextCommand: /create:changelog\n\n  # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n  qualityGates:\n    - id: evidence\n      label: Evidence\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - evidence-completeness\n        - no-inference-only\n      rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n    - id: scope\n      label: Scope\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - scope-alignment\n      rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n    - id: coverage\n      label: Coverage\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - severity-coverage\n        - cross-reference\n      rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n\n  # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n  convergence:\n    defaults:\n      maxIterations: 7\n      convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n      stuckThreshold: 2\n    signals:\n      - id: rolling-average\n        weight: 0.30\n        description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n      - id: mad-noise-floor\n        weight: 0.25\n        description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n      - id: dimension-coverage\n        weight: 0.45\n        description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n    severityMath:\n      refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n      p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n      noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n    coverageAge:\n      minStabilizationPasses: 1\n    thresholds:\n      rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n      noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n      compositeStopScore: 0.60\n\n  lifecycleModes:\n    - id: new\n      description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n    - id: resume\n      description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n    - id: restart\n      description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n    - id: fork\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n    - id: completed-continue\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n\n  lineageFields:\n    - sessionId\n    - parentSessionId\n    - lineageMode\n    - generation\n    - continuedFromRun\n\n  reducer:\n    enabled: true\n    inputs:\n      - latestJSONLDelta\n      - newIterationFile\n      - priorReducedState\n    outputs:\n      - findingsRegistry\n      - dashboardMetrics\n      - strategyUpdates\n    failureModes:\n      malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n      missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n      schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n    idempotent: true\n\n  releaseReadinessStates:\n    - id: in-progress\n      description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n    - id: converged\n      description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n    - id: release-blocking\n      description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n\n  # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n  # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n  crossReferenceProtocols:\n    - id: spec_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n      partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n      failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n    - id: checklist_evidence\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n      partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n      failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n    - id: skill_agent\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n      partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n      failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n    - id: agent_cross_runtime\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [agent]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n      partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n      failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n    - id: feature_catalog_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n      partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n      failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n    - id: playbook_capability\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":481,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","time":{"start":1782918969366,"end":1782918969380}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f3928188191b8e5bb78712e98b7"}},"id":"prt_f1e407813001opqnV0C5WiVNq5","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782918969383,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sNLUKIvCfveQpIZjIOhiXlIS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n7:   - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n8:   - \"review stuck detection\"\n9:   - \"composite convergence vote\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.21\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Convergence\n16: \n17: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n26: \n27: | Outcome | Meaning |\n28: |---------|---------|\n29: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n30: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n31: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n32: \n33: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n34: \n35: Release-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n36: - `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n37: - `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n38: - `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n39: \n40: When the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n41: \n42: ### When to Use\n43: \n44: - Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n45: - Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n46: - Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n47: - Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n48: \n49: ### Key Defaults\n50: \n51: | Setting | Value | Purpose |\n52: |---------|-------|---------|\n53: | `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n54: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n55: | `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n56: | `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n57: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n58: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n59: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n60: \n61: ### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n62: \n63: `convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n64: \n65: **Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n66: \n67: | Skill | Default | Signal |\n68: |---|---|---|\n69: | `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n70: | `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n71: | `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n72: \n73: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n74: \n75: ### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n76: \n77: > **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n78: \n79: For review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n80: \n81: | Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n82: |---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n83: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n84: | `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n85: | `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n86: \n87: When implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n88: \n89: ### Shared Stop Contract\n90: \n91: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n92: \n93: #### stopReason Enum\n94: \n95: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n96: |--------------|---------|\n97: | `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n98: | `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n99: | `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n100: | `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n101: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n102: | `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n103: | `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n104: \n105: #### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n106: \n107: `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n108: \n109: ```json\n110: {\n111:   \"type\": \"event\",\n112:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n113:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n114:   \"run\": 5,\n115:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n116:   \"gateResults\": {\n117:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n118:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n119:       \"pass\": false,\n120:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n121:       \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n122:     },\n123:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n124:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n125:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n126:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n127:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n128:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n129:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n130:   },\n131:   \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n132:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n133:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n134:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n135:   \"generation\": 1\n136: }\n137: ```\n138: \n139: - `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n140: - `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n141: - `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n142: - `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n143: - When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n144: \n145: ### Decision Priority\n146: \n147: Checks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n148: \n149: 1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n150: 2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n151: 3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n152: 4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n153: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n154: 6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## 2. HARD STOPS\n159: \n160: Hard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n161: \n162: ### Max Iterations Reached\n163: \n164: ```\n165: if len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n166:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n167: ```\n168: \n169: The loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n170: \n171: ### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n172: \n173: ```\n174: if coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n175:   if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n176:     if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n177:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n178: ```\n179: \n180: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n185: \n186: Identifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n187: \n188: ```\n189: function countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n190:   count = 0\n191:   for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n192:     if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n193:     if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n194:     if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n195:       count += 1\n196:     else:\n197:       break\n198:   return count\n199: ```\n200: \n201: **Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n202: \n203: **Status exclusions:**\n204: - `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n205: - `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n206: \n207: When `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n208: \n209: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n214: \n215: Three independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n216: \n217: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n218: |--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n219: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n220: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n221: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n222: \n223: ### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n224: \n225: Averages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n226: \n227: ```\n228: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n229:   recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n230:   avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n231:   rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n235: \n236: Robust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n237: \n238: ```\n239: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n240:   allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n241:   med = median(allRatios)\n242:   mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n243:   noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n244:   madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n248: \n249: Highest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n250: \n251: ```\n252: dimensionStop =\n253:   dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n254:   AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n255:   AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n256: ```\n257: \n258: The latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n259: \n260: ### Weighted Vote\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 585. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.21\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.21\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nConvergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n| **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n| **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n\nConvergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n\nRelease-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n- `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n- `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n- `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n\nWhen the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n- Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n- Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n- Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n\n### Key Defaults\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n| `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n\n`convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n\n**Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n\n| Skill | Default | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n| `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n| `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n\n### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n\n> **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n\nFor review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n\n| Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n| `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n| `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n\nWhen implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n\n### Shared Stop Contract\n\nEvery terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n#### stopReason Enum\n\n| `stopReason` | Meaning |\n|--------------|---------|\n| `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n| `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n| `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n| `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n| `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n\n#### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n\n`step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n- `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n- `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n- `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n- When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n\n### Decision Priority\n\nChecks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n\n1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HARD STOPS\n\nHard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n\n### Max Iterations Reached\n\n```\nif len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n  return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n```\n\nThe loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n\n### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n\n```\nif coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n  if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n    if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n      return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n```\n\nTriggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n\nIdentifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n\n```\nfunction countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n  count = 0\n  for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n    if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n    if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n    if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n      count += 1\n    else:\n      break\n  return count\n```\n\n**Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n**Status exclusions:**\n- `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n- `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n\nWhen `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n\nThe recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n\nThree independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n\n### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n\nAverages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n  recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n  avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n  rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n```\n\n### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n\nRobust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n  allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n  med = median(allRatios)\n  mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n  noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n  madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\n### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n\nHighest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n\n```\ndimensionStop =\n  dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n  AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n  AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n```\n\nThe latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n\n### Weighted Vote","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":585,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1782918969362,"end":1782918969381}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b2e6fa07934fb27016a452f39281081919e0243b4ad13c53b"}},"id":"prt_f1e40780e001EPmLyuvCEjVz27","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e400bb4001S0aKuyRARppHiK"}}
