{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117543,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4AiWePPncTRHnFUW3taN757X","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","offset":420,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n420: \n421: Related skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n426: \n427: ### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n428: \n429: Council alignment is complete when:\n430: \n431: - ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n432: - ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n433: - ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n434: - ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n435: - ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n436: \n437: ### Quality Targets\n438: \n439: - **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.\n440: - **Routing**: Section 3 is the only authoritative routing source.\n441: - **Reference shape**: reference filenames are snake_case and intro sections are short.\n442: - **Playbook coverage**: manual testing package has 32 scenarios across 9 categories.\n443: - **Boundary discipline**: graph rows never replace `ai-council/**` artifacts and council seats do not mutate graph storage directly.\n444: \n\n(Showing lines 420-444 of 491. Use offset=445 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n\nCouncil alignment is complete when:\n\n- ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n- ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n- ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n- ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n- ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n\n### Quality Targets\n\n- **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","text":"\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n\nCouncil alignment is complete when:\n\n- ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n- ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n- ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n- ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n- ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n\n### Quality Targets\n\n- **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.\n- **Routing**: Section 3 is the only authoritative routing source.\n- **Reference shape**: reference filenames are snake_case and intro sections are short.\n- **Playbook coverage**: manual testing package has 32 scenarios across 9 categories.\n- **Boundary discipline**: graph rows never replace `ai-council/**` artifacts and council seats do not mutate graph storage directly.\n","lineStart":420,"lineEnd":444,"totalLines":491,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782919117532,"end":1782919117541}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd78ec819198eb52c5a0d30687"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bad6001gaDqpyDMA3QUE9","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117638,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xoBFh7brLwA7hMo2XnJ5Xpiy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/structure/output_schema.md","offset":20,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/structure/output_schema.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: \n21: This document is the single source of truth for the `@deep-ai-council` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT. The agent body uses §8 to tell the planning LEAF what report to return; `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs` uses this contract to parse that report and persist packet-local `ai-council/` artifacts.\n22: \n23: The report remains markdown, not JSON. The helper accepts normal heading variation, extracts the strict-required sections, and degrades gracefully for optional narrative sections.\n24: \n25: Cross-references:\n26: \n27: - Agent body: `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT and §16 Caller Persistence Protocol\n28: - Runtime mirrors: `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`\n29: - Helper: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs`\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. REQUIREDNESS MATRIX\n34: \n35: | Section name | Strict-required | Helper behavior on missing |\n36: | --- | --- | --- |\n37: | Council Composition | Y | `parseCouncilReport()` returns `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |\n38: | Per-seat sections or composition-table seat rows | Y | `ok:false` when no `Seat N` headings and no composition rows exist |\n39: | Recommended Plan | Y | `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |\n\n(Showing lines 20-39 of 135. Use offset=40 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nThis document is the single source of truth for the `@deep-ai-council` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT. The agent body uses §8 to tell the planning LEAF what report to return; `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs` uses this contract to parse that report and persist packet-local `ai-council/` artifacts.\n\nThe report remains markdown, not JSON. The helper accepts normal heading variation, extracts the strict-required sections, and degrades gracefully for optional narrative sections.\n\nCross-references:\n\n- Agent body: `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT and §16 Caller Persistence Protocol\n- Runtime mirrors: `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`\n- Helper: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs`\n\n---\n\n## 2. REQUIREDNESS MATRIX\n\n| Section name | Strict-required | Helper behavior on missing |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Council Composition | Y | `parseCouncilReport()` returns `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |\n| Per-seat sections or composition-table seat rows | Y | `ok:false` when no `Seat N` headings and no composition rows exist |\n| Recommended Plan | Y | `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/structure/output_schema.md","text":"\nThis document is the single source of truth for the `@deep-ai-council` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT. The agent body uses §8 to tell the planning LEAF what report to return; `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs` uses this contract to parse that report and persist packet-local `ai-council/` artifacts.\n\nThe report remains markdown, not JSON. The helper accepts normal heading variation, extracts the strict-required sections, and degrades gracefully for optional narrative sections.\n\nCross-references:\n\n- Agent body: `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md` §8 OUTPUT FORMAT and §16 Caller Persistence Protocol\n- Runtime mirrors: `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`\n- Helper: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs`\n\n---\n\n## 2. REQUIREDNESS MATRIX\n\n| Section name | Strict-required | Helper behavior on missing |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Council Composition | Y | `parseCouncilReport()` returns `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |\n| Per-seat sections or composition-table seat rows | Y | `ok:false` when no `Seat N` headings and no composition rows exist |\n| Recommended Plan | Y | `ok:false`; CLI exits 1 before writes |","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":39,"totalLines":135,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/structure/output_schema.md","time":{"start":1782919117613,"end":1782919117636}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd79088191a3952fefd6e110b7"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bb1c0014lt46muBMp0nfi","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117639,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_GqnjkbUovQVYpHSE4Y1dK5yS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":700,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n700: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n701: |----------|------|---------|\n702: | Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n703: | Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n704: | Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n705: | Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n706: | Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n707: \n708: ### Workflow Files\n709: \n710: | Mode | Path |\n711: |------|------|\n712: | Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n713: | Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n714: \n715: ### Agent\n716: \n717: | Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n718: |-------|-------------|------------|\n719: | `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n720: \n721: Runtime paths:\n722: - OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n723: - Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n724: - OpenCode: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.toml`\n725: \n726: ---\n727: \n728: ## Executor Selection Contract\n729: \n730: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n731: \n732: ### Invariants\n733: \n734: Every executor path MUST satisfy:\n735: \n736: 1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n737: 2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n738: 3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n739: \n\n(Showing lines 700-739 of 766. Use offset=740 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n| Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n| Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n| Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n\n### Workflow Files\n\n| Mode | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n\n### Agent\n\n| Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n| Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n| Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n| Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n\n### Workflow Files\n\n| Mode | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n\n### Agent\n\n| Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n\nRuntime paths:\n- OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n- OpenCode: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.toml`\n\n---\n\n## Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n\n### Invariants\n\nEvery executor path MUST satisfy:\n\n1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n","lineStart":700,"lineEnd":739,"totalLines":766,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1782919117619,"end":1782919117638}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd79148191a90cc911982de3c4"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bb31001a7fxQLYI0c1KWl","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117716,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_w7H0eAFsiPcj9Tjc3vdn9Z8v","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md","offset":48,"limit":16},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n48: \n49: ## 3. MATRIX\n50: \n51: | Runtime | Mirror Path | Tool Surface | Hook Bootstrap | Schema Adaptation | Fallback Bridge Eligible | Notes |\n52: |---------|-------------|--------------|----------------|-------------------|--------------------------|-------|\n53: | OpenCode / Copilot | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory | Yes (plugin) | Low | Yes | OpenCode uses plugin-based hooks (`@opencode-ai/plugin`); Copilot uses repo-local session-start banner hook. |\n54: | Claude | `.claude/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, MCP memory | Yes | Low | Yes | Default command YAML example path points here, but behavior is runtime-agnostic. |\n55: | OpenCode | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.toml` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory MCP | Yes | Medium | Yes | TOML mirror must keep the same lifecycle/reducer contract as the Markdown mirrors. |\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 4. ADAPTATION RULES\n60: \n61: Allowed runtime adaptation:\n62: \n63: - Tool names and transport details may change per runtime.\n\n(Showing lines 48-63 of 97. Use offset=64 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n## 3. MATRIX\n\n| Runtime | Mirror Path | Tool Surface | Hook Bootstrap | Schema Adaptation | Fallback Bridge Eligible | Notes |\n|---------|-------------|--------------|----------------|-------------------|--------------------------|-------|\n| OpenCode / Copilot | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory | Yes (plugin) | Low | Yes | OpenCode uses plugin-based hooks (`@opencode-ai/plugin`); Copilot uses repo-local session-start banner hook. |\n| Claude | `.claude/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, MCP memory | Yes | Low | Yes | Default command YAML example path points here, but behavior is runtime-agnostic. |\n| OpenCode | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.toml` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory MCP | Yes | Medium | Yes | TOML mirror must keep the same lifecycle/reducer contract as the Markdown mirrors. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ADAPTATION RULES\n\nAllowed runtime adaptation:\n\n- Tool names and transport details may change per runtime.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md","text":"\n## 3. MATRIX\n\n| Runtime | Mirror Path | Tool Surface | Hook Bootstrap | Schema Adaptation | Fallback Bridge Eligible | Notes |\n|---------|-------------|--------------|----------------|-------------------|--------------------------|-------|\n| OpenCode / Copilot | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory | Yes (plugin) | Low | Yes | OpenCode uses plugin-based hooks (`@opencode-ai/plugin`); Copilot uses repo-local session-start banner hook. |\n| Claude | `.claude/agents/deep-research.md` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, MCP memory | Yes | Low | Yes | Default command YAML example path points here, but behavior is runtime-agnostic. |\n| OpenCode | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.toml` | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit`, `Bash`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `WebFetch`, memory MCP | Yes | Medium | Yes | TOML mirror must keep the same lifecycle/reducer contract as the Markdown mirrors. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ADAPTATION RULES\n\nAllowed runtime adaptation:\n\n- Tool names and transport details may change per runtime.","lineStart":48,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":97,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md","time":{"start":1782919117709,"end":1782919117714}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd791c8191b896585c8f70d8d4"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bb36001g3E0rPHd8FGr4j","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117818,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jQCruEVaN70HFILek2J4Ugb0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","offset":372,"limit":24},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n372: **Agent:** `ai-council`\n373: **Use case:** 1 or 3\n374: \n375: ```text\n376: Plan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n377: \n378: Context: <one-paragraph context>\n379: Role: planning architect — no file modifications.\n380: Action: generate three distinct strategies, score each across the 5-dimension rubric, synthesize the optimal plan.\n381: Format: structured JSON plus a summary paragraph.\n382: Target: an implementation-ready plan that another agent can execute.\n383: ```\n384: \n385: ```bash\n386: opencode run \\\n387:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n388:   --agent ai-council \\\n389:   --variant high \\\n390:   --format json \\\n391:   --dir /repo \\\n392:   \"<prompt>\" 2>&1\n393: ```\n394: \n395: ---\n\n(Showing lines 372-395 of 647. Use offset=396 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"**Agent:** `ai-council`\n**Use case:** 1 or 3\n\n```text\nPlan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n\nContext: <one-paragraph context>\nRole: planning architect — no file modifications.\nAction: generate three distinct strategies, score each across the 5-dimension rubric, synthesize the optimal plan.\nFormat: structured JSON plus a summary paragraph.\nTarget: an implementation-ready plan that another agent can execute.\n```\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent ai-council \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir /repo \\","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","text":"**Agent:** `ai-council`\n**Use case:** 1 or 3\n\n```text\nPlan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n\nContext: <one-paragraph context>\nRole: planning architect — no file modifications.\nAction: generate three distinct strategies, score each across the 5-dimension rubric, synthesize the optimal plan.\nFormat: structured JSON plus a summary paragraph.\nTarget: an implementation-ready plan that another agent can execute.\n```\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent ai-council \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir /repo \\\n  \"<prompt>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n---","lineStart":372,"lineEnd":395,"totalLines":647,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","time":{"start":1782919117806,"end":1782919117815}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd79388191b1c60d0aa531192e"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bbec001RlfJLiL3EbA6T4","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117822,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZqGn4LhC0GZF9VZCv4IMZpaQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\"\n3: description: \"This scenario validates the ai-council planning-only agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` produces multiple distinct strategies scored across a rubric and respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\"\n4: version: 1.3.0.3\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\n8: \n9: This document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors and metadata for `CO-017`.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n14: \n15: This scenario validates the Ultra-think multi-strategy planning agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` generates at least 3 distinct solution strategies, scores each across a multi-dimension rubric, recommends one with rationale, AND respects the planning-only constraint documented in `references/agent_delegation.md` §7 (no file modifications).\n16: \n17: ### Why This Matters\n18: \n19: `ai-council` is the canonical multi-strategy planning architect. Its value depends on two contracts: produce diverse, well-scored strategies (not a single linear plan). Never write files (planning-only LEAF constraint). If either contract breaks, the agent loses its differentiator from `general` and its safety story for use in pre-implementation planning. This test validates both contracts simultaneously.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n24: \n25: Operators run the exact prompt and command sequence for `CO-017` and confirm the expected signals without contradictory evidence.\n26: \n27: - Objective: Confirm `--agent ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct strategies scored on at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND no file modifications occur.\n28: - Real user request: `Use opencode run with --agent ai-council to compare 3 strategies for migrating a small JS module from CommonJS to ESM. Confirm the response has 3 strategies, each scored on at least 3 dimensions, an explicit recommendation, AND no files were modified.`\n29: - RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.`\n30: - Expected execution process: External-AI orchestrator snapshots a few sentinel file mtimes, dispatches with `--agent ai-council`, validates the response presents three distinct strategies with scoring across at least three dimensions and an explicit recommendation and confirms the sentinel mtimes are unchanged.\n31: - Expected signals: Dispatch exits 0. Response contains exactly or close to 3 distinct strategies. Each strategy has at least 3 dimension scores. An explicit recommendation appears with rationale. Sentinel file mtimes are unchanged. No Edit/Write tool.calls appear in the JSON event stream.\n32: - Desired user-visible outcome: Verdict naming the recommended strategy, the dimension count and the safety status.\n33: - Pass/fail: PASS if exit 0 AND >= 3 distinct strategies AND >= 3 dimensions per strategy AND explicit recommendation AND no Edit/Write tool.calls AND sentinel mtimes unchanged. FAIL if any check fails.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n38: \n39: ### Recommended Orchestration Process\n40: \n41: 1. Restate the user request in plain user language.\n42: 2. Snapshot mtimes of a few sentinel files.\n43: 3. Dispatch with `--agent ai-council` and the multi-strategy planning prompt.\n44: 4. Validate response has 3 strategies, dimensions and recommendation.\n45: 5. Re-snapshot sentinel mtimes and confirm unchanged.\n46: 6. Validate no Edit/Write tool.calls in the JSON event stream.\n47: 7. Return a verdict naming recommendation, dimension count and safety status.\n48: \n49: | Feature ID | Feature Name | Scenario Name / Objective | Exact Prompt | Exact Command Sequence | Expected Signals | Evidence | Pass/Fail Criteria | Failure Triage |\n50: |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n51: | CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent ai-council --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n52: \n53: ### Optional Supplemental Checks\n54: \n55: For rubric depth, ask the agent to produce a 5x5 markdown table with strategies as rows and dimensions as columns. Confirm every cell has a non-empty score. This is the \"ideal output shape\" for ai-council dispatches and stresses the agent's ability to produce structured output.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n60: \n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 82. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\"\ndescription: \"This scenario validates the ai-council planning-only agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` produces multiple distinct strategies scored across a rubric and respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\"\nversion: 1.3.0.3\n---\n\n# CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\n\nThis document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors and metadata for `CO-017`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario validates the Ultra-think multi-strategy planning agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` generates at least 3 distinct solution strategies, scores each across a multi-dimension rubric, recommends one with rationale, AND respects the planning-only constraint documented in `references/agent_delegation.md` §7 (no file modifications).\n\n### Why This Matters\n\n`ai-council` is the canonical multi-strategy planning architect. Its value depends on two contracts: produce diverse, well-scored strategies (not a single linear plan). Never write files (planning-only LEAF constraint). If either contract breaks, the agent loses its differentiator from `general` and its safety story for use in pre-implementation planning. This test validates both contracts simultaneously.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\"\ndescription: \"This scenario validates the ai-council planning-only agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` produces multiple distinct strategies scored across a rubric and respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\"\nversion: 1.3.0.3\n---\n\n# CO-017 -- Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\n\nThis document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors and metadata for `CO-017`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario validates the Ultra-think multi-strategy planning agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent ai-council` generates at least 3 distinct solution strategies, scores each across a multi-dimension rubric, recommends one with rationale, AND respects the planning-only constraint documented in `references/agent_delegation.md` §7 (no file modifications).\n\n### Why This Matters\n\n`ai-council` is the canonical multi-strategy planning architect. Its value depends on two contracts: produce diverse, well-scored strategies (not a single linear plan). Never write files (planning-only LEAF constraint). If either contract breaks, the agent loses its differentiator from `general` and its safety story for use in pre-implementation planning. This test validates both contracts simultaneously.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\nOperators run the exact prompt and command sequence for `CO-017` and confirm the expected signals without contradictory evidence.\n\n- Objective: Confirm `--agent ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct strategies scored on at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND no file modifications occur.\n- Real user request: `Use opencode run with --agent ai-council to compare 3 strategies for migrating a small JS module from CommonJS to ESM. Confirm the response has 3 strategies, each scored on at least 3 dimensions, an explicit recommendation, AND no files were modified.`\n- RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.`\n- Expected execution process: External-AI orchestrator snapshots a few sentinel file mtimes, dispatches with `--agent ai-council`, validates the response presents three distinct strategies with scoring across at least three dimensions and an explicit recommendation and confirms the sentinel mtimes are unchanged.\n- Expected signals: Dispatch exits 0. Response contains exactly or close to 3 distinct strategies. Each strategy has at least 3 dimension scores. An explicit recommendation appears with rationale. Sentinel file mtimes are unchanged. No Edit/Write tool.calls appear in the JSON event stream.\n- Desired user-visible outcome: Verdict naming the recommended strategy, the dimension count and the safety status.\n- Pass/fail: PASS if exit 0 AND >= 3 distinct strategies AND >= 3 dimensions per strategy AND explicit recommendation AND no Edit/Write tool.calls AND sentinel mtimes unchanged. FAIL if any check fails.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n### Recommended Orchestration Process\n\n1. Restate the user request in plain user language.\n2. Snapshot mtimes of a few sentinel files.\n3. Dispatch with `--agent ai-council` and the multi-strategy planning prompt.\n4. Validate response has 3 strategies, dimensions and recommendation.\n5. Re-snapshot sentinel mtimes and confirm unchanged.\n6. Validate no Edit/Write tool.calls in the JSON event stream.\n7. Return a verdict naming recommendation, dimension count and safety status.\n\n| Feature ID | Feature Name | Scenario Name / Objective | Exact Prompt | Exact Command Sequence | Expected Signals | Evidence | Pass/Fail Criteria | Failure Triage |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent ai-council --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n### Optional Supplemental Checks\n\nFor rubric depth, ask the agent to produce a 5x5 markdown table with strategies as rows and dimensions as columns. Confirm every cell has a non-empty score. This is the \"ideal output shape\" for ai-council dispatches and stresses the agent's ability to produce structured output.\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE FILES\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":82,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md","time":{"start":1782919117803,"end":1782919117818}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd79308191a847d737ad4e5e67"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bbe9001DJCAan0rv4pU4O","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919117822,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yUsVeQhxW16mIej0xZpHXLnv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","offset":356,"limit":72},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n356: > **Feature File:** [CO-012](03--multi-provider/variant-levels-comparison.md)\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## 10. AGENT ROUTING (`CO-013..CO-017`, `CO-032..CO-034`)\n361: \n362: This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n363: \n364: ### CO-013 | General agent default route\n365: \n366: #### Description\n367: \n368: Verify `--agent general` loads the project's general agent definition from `.opencode/agents/general.md` and the dispatched session demonstrates implementation-style behavior with full read/write/dispatch tool permissions.\n369: \n370: #### Scenario Contract\n371: \n372: Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor verifying the general-agent default route, dispatch --agent general with a prompt that requires a Read tool call against a small project file and a multi-step reasoning summary. Verify the JSON event stream shows a tool.call for Read, the response references content from the file and the agent slug general is identified in the session metadata.\n373: \n374: Expected signals: Exit 0. Read tool.call appears. Agent slug `general` in session metadata. Response references the read file's content.\n375: \n376: #### Test Execution\n377: \n378: > **Feature File:** [CO-013](04--agent-routing/general-agent-default.md)\n379: \n380: ### CO-014 | Context LEAF agent (read-only)\n381: \n382: #### Description\n383: \n384: Verify `--agent context` produces a structured architecture map of a target directory AND enforces the LEAF read-only constraint (no sub-dispatches, no writes, mtime-stable target files).\n385: \n386: #### Scenario Contract\n387: \n388: Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor needing a safe read-only architecture map of an unfamiliar module, dispatch --agent context against .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/. Snapshot mtimes before and after. Verify the response identifies SKILL.md as the entry point, references/ and assets/ as supporting structure and that no mtimes changed and no Edit/Write tool.call events appear.\n389: \n390: Expected signals: Exit 0. Mtime diff is empty. No Edit/Write tool.calls. Response identifies entry point + supporting structure.\n391: \n392: #### Test Execution\n393: \n394: > **Feature File:** [CO-014](04--agent-routing/context-leaf-agent.md)\n395: \n396: ### CO-015 | Review agent security audit\n397: \n398: #### Description\n399: \n400: Verify `--agent review` produces severity-tagged security findings (P0/P1/P2 OR critical/high/medium/low) with file:line citations against a target file with an obvious vulnerability, AND respects the read-only sandbox constraint.\n401: \n402: #### Scenario Contract\n403: \n404: Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor wanting an independent security audit before merging, write a small TS file with at least one obvious vulnerability to /tmp/co-015-target.ts. Dispatch --agent review against the file with an OWASP checklist (XSS, injection, auth bypass, hardcoded secrets). Verify the response surfaces findings with severity tags and line references and that the target file mtime does NOT change.\n405: \n406: Expected signals: Exit 0. Severity tag present. Line reference present. Target file mtime unchanged. Zero Edit/Write tool.calls.\n407: \n408: #### Test Execution\n409: \n410: > **Feature File:** [CO-015](04--agent-routing/review-agent-security-audit.md)\n411: \n412: \n413: ### CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\n414: \n415: #### Description\n416: \n417: Verify `--agent ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct solution strategies scored across at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\n418: \n419: #### Scenario Contract\n420: \n421: Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale and does NOT modify any files in the repo.\n422: \n423: Expected signals: Exit 0. Sentinel mtimes unchanged. Zero Edit/Write tool.calls. >=3 distinct strategies. >=3 dimensions scored. Explicit recommendation.\n424: \n425: #### Test Execution\n426: \n427: > **Feature File:** [CO-017](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)\n\n(Showing lines 356-427 of 862. Use offset=428 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"> **Feature File:** [CO-012](03--multi-provider/variant-levels-comparison.md)\n\n---\n\n## 10. AGENT ROUTING (`CO-013..CO-017`, `CO-032..CO-034`)\n\nThis category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n\n### CO-013 | General agent default route\n\n#### Description\n\nVerify `--agent general` loads the project's general agent definition from `.opencode/agents/general.md` and the dispatched session demonstrates implementation-style behavior with full read/write/dispatch tool permissions.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\n\nPrompt summary: As an external-AI conductor verifying the general-agent default route, dispatch --agent general with a prompt that requires a Read tool call against a small project file and a multi-step reasoning summary. Verify the JSON event stream shows a tool.call for Read, the response references content from the file and the agent slug general is identified in the session metadata.\n\nExpected signals: Exit 0. Read tool.call appears. Agent slug `general` in session metadata. Response references the read file's content.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","text":"> **Feature File:** [CO-012](03--multi-provider/variant-levels-comparison.md)\n\n---\n\n## 10. AGENT ROUTING (`CO-013..CO-017`, `CO-032..CO-034`)\n\nThis category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n\n### CO-013 | General agent default route\n\n#### Description\n\nVerify `--agent general` loads the project's general agent definition from `.opencode/agents/general.md` and the dispatched session demonstrates implementation-style behavior with full read/write/dispatch tool permissions.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\n\nPrompt summary: As an external-AI conductor verifying the general-agent default route, dispatch --agent general with a prompt that requires a Read tool call against a small project file and a multi-step reasoning summary. Verify the JSON event stream shows a tool.call for Read, the response references content from the file and the agent slug general is identified in the session metadata.\n\nExpected signals: Exit 0. Read tool.call appears. Agent slug `general` in session metadata. Response references the read file's content.\n\n#### Test Execution\n\n> **Feature File:** [CO-013](04--agent-routing/general-agent-default.md)\n\n### CO-014 | Context LEAF agent (read-only)\n\n#### Description\n\nVerify `--agent context` produces a structured architecture map of a target directory AND enforces the LEAF read-only constraint (no sub-dispatches, no writes, mtime-stable target files).\n\n#### Scenario Contract\n\nPrompt summary: As an external-AI conductor needing a safe read-only architecture map of an unfamiliar module, dispatch --agent context against .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/. Snapshot mtimes before and after. Verify the response identifies SKILL.md as the entry point, references/ and assets/ as supporting structure and that no mtimes changed and no Edit/Write tool.call events appear.\n\nExpected signals: Exit 0. Mtime diff is empty. No Edit/Write tool.calls. Response identifies entry point + supporting structure.\n\n#### Test Execution\n\n> **Feature File:** [CO-014](04--agent-routing/context-leaf-agent.md)\n\n### CO-015 | Review agent security audit\n\n#### Description\n\nVerify `--agent review` produces severity-tagged security findings (P0/P1/P2 OR critical/high/medium/low) with file:line citations against a target file with an obvious vulnerability, AND respects the read-only sandbox constraint.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\n\nPrompt summary: As an external-AI conductor wanting an independent security audit before merging, write a small TS file with at least one obvious vulnerability to /tmp/co-015-target.ts. Dispatch --agent review against the file with an OWASP checklist (XSS, injection, auth bypass, hardcoded secrets). Verify the response surfaces findings with severity tags and line references and that the target file mtime does NOT change.\n\nExpected signals: Exit 0. Severity tag present. Line reference present. Target file mtime unchanged. Zero Edit/Write tool.calls.\n\n#### Test Execution\n\n> **Feature File:** [CO-015](04--agent-routing/review-agent-security-audit.md)\n\n\n### CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning\n\n#### Description\n\nVerify `--agent ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct solution strategies scored across at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\n\n#### Scenario Contract\n\nPrompt summary: As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale and does NOT modify any files in the repo.\n\nExpected signals: Exit 0. Sentinel mtimes unchanged. Zero Edit/Write tool.calls. >=3 distinct strategies. >=3 dimensions scored. Explicit recommendation.\n\n#### Test Execution\n\n> **Feature File:** [CO-017](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)","lineStart":356,"lineEnd":427,"totalLines":862,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","time":{"start":1782919117785,"end":1782919117820}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a22bbb798445116016a452fcd792481918d27bc7c27568a5a"}},"id":"prt_f1e42bbcf0016BvBMlMACWirwA","sessionID":"ses_0e1c12f14ffe56Cs01FOXHPL99","messageID":"msg_f1e4255b60010vuNlFNylZfO9F"}}
